  - CVE-2020-35452: mod_auth_digest possible stack overflow by one null byte

  - CVE-2021-26690: mod_session NULL pointer dereference

  - CVE-2021-26691: mod_session response handling heap overflow|affected=Apache HTTP Server versions 2.4.0 to 2.4.46 on Linux.|impact=- CVE-2020-35452: A specially crafted Digest nonce can cause a
