  vulnerability in the 'mod_proxy' module.|insight=Apache's mod_proxy allows spaces in the :method of HTTP/2
  requests, enabling request line injection. If the back-end server tolerates trailing junk in the
  request line, this lets an attacker to bypass block rules.|affected=Apache HTTP Server version 2.4.17 through 2.4.48 running the
  mod_proxy module together with an enabled HTTP/2 protocol.|impact=|solution=Update to version 2.4.49 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
