        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H|summary=Apache HTTP Server is prone to multiple vulnerabilities.|insight=Apache HTTP server is prone to multiple vulnerabilities:

  - A malicious client could perform a DoS attack by flooding a connection with requests and
  basically never reading responses on the TCP connection. Depending on h2 worker dimensioning,
  it was possible to block those with relatively few connections. (CVE-2019-9517)

  - HTTP/2 very early pushes, for example configured with 'H2PushResource', could lead to
  an overwrite of memory in the pushing request's pool, leading to crashes. The memory
  copied is that of the configured push link header values, not data supplied by
  the client. (CVE-2019-10081)|affected=Apache HTTP Server version 2.4.20 to 2.4.39.|impact=|solution=Update to version 2.4.41 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 2.4.41 or later.</solution>
